OREON Hydraulic System Manual

Hydraulic systems require clean fluid, stable pressure, low water content, and correct filter
differential pressure. Degradation indicators include pump noise, actuator drift, pressure ripple,
fluid temperature above 70 C, foaming, seal leakage, and servo valve sticking.

Corrective actions: sample fluid, inspect filters, check pump inlet restriction, verify relief valve
setting, bleed air, repair leaks, and replace contaminated fluid.
